		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey, I also have an EKROM board here, but I was afraid it's pinout is completely different than all other NES pinouts because of MMC5 mapper (or at least for the PRG ROM). As a proof, Laser Invasion normally should have a 28 pin PRG ROM because its 128 KB, but no they have a 32-pin one, proof that MMC5 carts are different from all others.
<br />
<br />I guess the guy who wrote NESHLA (I guess his pseudo was brian provinco or something similar) traced the pinouts of MMC5 chips. I hope this will answer your questions : <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://bripro.com/low/mappers/index.php?page=nes-mmc5_rompin">http://bripro.com/low/mappers/index.php ... mc5_rompin</a><!-- m -->

		

