	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Oh yeah the other guy doesn't seem to be verygood at talking english, nor am I but yeah if you're screwed....
<br />The other guy claims that MMC5 pinouts are the same as all others, but honnestly I don't have such a conviction, I'll check it someday.
<br />
<br />To rewire your rom, look at the old pinout, and the new pinout, and mark the differences. Then, modify your board to that the traces to the old pinouts are cut and are wired according to the new pinout instead. Altenarively, bend up all pins leading to a pin where the old pinout doesn't match the new one, and connect the bed up to the signal where it should be going.
<br />This has the advantage of being less confusing, but in the end that's less proper work, and the probabiltity of 2 wires short-cuircit themselves is higher.
<br />Of course if you don't have the old pinout that's another problem.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


